The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 27 September is 75,486 (8,700.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 22 September, there were 2,046 new confirmed cases (235.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 15 September, there were 1,566 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 31% (480 extra cases).
